Angla Burger

because the container is serving the old build.

Why?

Remember your Dockerfile?

It probably looks something like

FROM node:22-alpine AS builder

...

RUN npm run build

FROM nginx:alpine

COPY --from=builder /app/dist /usr/share/nginx/html

This line is the key:

COPY --from=builder /app/dist /usr/share/nginx/html

At the moment you ran

docker build

Docker copied that exact dist folder into the image.

From then on...

The image is frozen.

It doesn't know your React files changed.

If you want Docker to show your changes

You need to rebuild the image.

docker build -t angla-burger-frontend .

Then recreate the container:

docker stop angla-ui
docker rm angla-ui

docker run -d -p 8080:80 --name angla-ui angla-burger-frontend

Now Nginx serves the new build.

Here's the mental model I want you to remember

Think of it like baking a cake.

Your React source code is the recipe.

src/

Running

npm run build

is baking the cake.

dist/

Running

docker build

is putting that cake into a sealed box.

Docker Image

Running

docker run

is putting the boxed cake on a store shelf.

Container

If you change the recipe after the cake is already boxed...

🍰 The cake inside the box doesn't magically change.

You have to:

Bake a new cake (npm run build).
Box it again (docker build).
Replace the old box on the shelf (docker run after removing/restarting the old container).

